                         <br><h4>2.Main function:</h4>
                         <p class="text-justify">
                           Remember program always starts from the main function.It defines from where program should 
                           start.Now you can say first you need to add a header file then you need to define or add the
                           main function.
                         </p>
                         <h5>Syntax of including main function:</h5>

<pre class="prettyprint">
<code>#include&lt;stdio.h&gt;
int main()</code></pre>    
                      <h4>3.Program Body:</h4>   
                      <p class="txt-justify">
                        Program body starts with the opening curly brackets <b>{</b> right after the <b>main function</b>  and end
                          with the closing carlibrace <b>}</b> .In between the opening and closing curly brackets we need to write 
                          the codes that we wants.
                      </p>

                      <h5>Lets see how to write:</h5>
<pre class="prettyprint">
<code> #include&lt;stdio.h&gt;
  int main()
  {//start program body
    int a = 5;
    printf("Number is: %d",a);
    return 0;
  }//end program body</code></pre>
  <h5>Output:</h5>
  <pre class="prettyprint">Number is: 5</code></pre>
       
